OMG not expensive, great quality, exceptional service by the owner couple. Never expected or seen such three qualities in any Chinese or Korean restaurants in the entire USA(Actually it was HongKong style). Corona time so I was able to be seated to eat the smaller plates that cost $4~$6 each and you can order several. Owner came to pour tea several times and ask how food is. Gentle and not in an intruding way like how some waiters barking in the middle of conversation. 2 big Manapua and Two Lotus leaf rice were only $6 each. Three Shrimp dumplings $6 and REAL shrimps-fat,fresh, juicy. I wonder how they make money off? Perhaps by having ppl like me come over again and again. The quality of food is SUPERB. Downtown Chinatown or any similar places sell the same thing but more expensive, lesser quality, and all the sales people have not-so-great attitude. There is another famous Chinese restaurant in Honolulu  that almost all Chinese ppl on the island go. But they are not like the Mandalay. There I get stomachache from grease and not like the service. I guess it's just Chinese-American-food business-culture. I rarely write reviews but I'm bringing my friends here and eat some other dishes too. OH AND OWNER REPLACED A DISH I DIDNT LIKE. I didn't expect anything just said all food is great except chicken feet. And she made something else. I was going to pay for it anyway but again super surprised and exuberant people.

We had our daughter’s Surprise 40th Birthday Party here and chose a set menu for 8 tables of 10.  The staff was accommodating n gave us a Sign In table, a table for the cakes and a table for a “Make Your Own Trail Mix”!  The food was delicious and bountiful as there was enough leftovers for Folks to take home.  My favorite was the Peking Duck and the Honey Walnut Shrimp but we also had Dim Sum and Sweet and Sour Pork, Taro Puffs, Veggies, Noodles for a long life.and Custard Tarts.  The presentation of the dishes was nice and the food was delivered in a timely fashion.  The Staff helped to serve and psss out the cake and ice cream too!  I would definitely do another Celebration here!

If you rather do takeout, there's another entrance a few steps down (don't walk past Alii Place, you've gone too far). You can pick up to 3 choices of sides and get it with fried rice, chow mein, or chow funn. This lunch will cost you less than $10 and you'll be stuffed.
